summary: Been trying to practice watercolors everyday here lately. (Specifically faces because I suck at those.) These are from the same...
caption: Been trying to practice watercolors everyday here lately. (Specifically faces because I suck at those.) These are from the same week but they look like they are done by different artists. The first one was done today after not sleeping the night before and thus not being able to concentrate, the second was done two days ago when I was well rested and in a creative mindset, and the third was done four days ago while dealing with stress and (mild) hallucinations. This is what artists mean when they say they don’t feel like they can do art sometimes. Being in a creative mental state is crucial to making good art. You can’t force creativity and you can’t work under certain conditions.
